.cs 3 on
.item 'SHOW NETWORK Command' 'Updated on 12/15/82 by LSO'
.boxon
SHOW NETWORK [[front-end|CONSOLE|ASYNC|PDP|SNA|VIRTUAL]
             [DIRECT|LEASED|DIAL]|ALL] [collect-options]
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
The SHOW NETWORK command displays the status of all the front ends currently
connected to the system.  A "front end" is a communications controller for a
group of terminals.

.* SELECT 'SHOW NETWORK Command Options'
.us Option Descriptions

.* OPTION FRONT-END
.optix front-end
front-end\\\\\\\the name of a particular communications controller (e.g.,
                1270A).

.* OPTION CONSOLE
.optix CONSOLE
CONSOLE\\\\\\\\\ports connected to the operator consoles.

.* OPTION ASYNC
.optix ASYNC
ASYNC\\\\\\\\\\\asynchronous ports.

.* OPTION PDP
.optix PDP
PDP\\\\\\\\\\\\\ports connected via the PDP front ends.

.* OPTION SNA
.optix SNA
SNA\\\\\\\\\\\\\ports connected via the SNA (VTAM) network.

.* OPTION VIRTUAL
.optix VIRTUAL
VIRTUAL\\\\\\\\\ports being used as "virtual terminals" (i.e., batch).

.* OPTION DIRECT
.optix DIRECT
DIRECT\\\\\\\\\\ports connected directly (terminals with dedicated ports).

.* OPTION LEASED
.optix LEASED
LEASED\\\\\\\\\\leased direct ports (i.e., bulk rate).

.* OPTION DIAL
.optix DIAL
DIAL\\\\\\\\\\\\ports connected via the dial-up ports.

.* OPTION ALL
.optix ALL
ALL\\\\\\\\\\\\\all ports connected to all the front ends.

.* OPTION COLLECT-OPTIONS,BY,KEEP,NOCLEAR,NOCLR,CLEAR,CLR,WARN,NOWARN
.optix collect-options
collect-options\allow you to insert the system response to the SHOW NETWORK
                command into your active file.  Type HELP COLLECT-OPTIONS for
                a description of these options.
.cs 3 off
